<mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mn>96500</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>mole <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></math>-factor <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mn>96500</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mn>96500</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>96500</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>93</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (01 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":29507,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Electrochemistry","question":"","options":["$29.5 \\times 10^{-2}$","10","$1 \\times 10^{10}$","$1 \\times 10^{-10}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"The equilibrium constant is related to the standard emf of cell by the expression\n$\\log K=E_{\\text {cell }}^0 \\times \\frac{n}{0.059}=0.295 \\times \\frac{2}{0.059}$\n$\\log \\mathrm{K}=\\frac{590}{59}=10$ or $\\mathrm{K}=1 \\times 10^{-10}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":29311,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Electrochemistry","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Given : Concentration of $\\mathrm{NaOH}=0.2 \\%(\\mathrm{w} / \\mathrm{v})$<br />$\\therefore 0.2 \\mathrm{~g}$ of NaOH in 100 ml of solution.<br />Molarity of NaOH solution<br />$\\begin{array}{r}<br />=\\frac{\\text { moles of solute }}{\\mathrm{V}_{\\mathrm{ml}}} \\times 1000 \\\\<br>=\\frac{0.2 / 40}{100} \\times 1000==\\frac{0.2}{40 \\times 100} \\times 1000=\\frac{2}{40} \\mathrm{M}<br />\\end{array}$<br />Given resistivity of solution $=870 \\mathrm{~m}$ ohm m $=870 \\times 10^{-3} \\mathrm{ohm} \\mathrm{m}$<br />$=870 \\times 10^{-3} \\times 10 \\mathrm{ohm} \\mathrm{dm}$<br />$=870 \\times 10^{-2}$ ohm dm<br />$=8.7$ ohm dm<br />Now conductivity<br />$\\mathrm{K}=\\frac{1}{\\rho}=\\frac{1}{8.7} \\mathrm{ohm}^{-1} \\mathrm{dm}^{-1}$<br />Now molar conductivity of solution is<br />$\\begin{aligned}<br />& \\lambda_{\\mathrm{m}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{K}}{\\mathrm{M}}=\\frac{\\frac{1}{8.7}}{\\frac{2}{40}}=\\frac{40}{2 \\times 8.7}=2.29 \\mathrm{~S} \\mathrm{dm}^2 \\mathrm{~mol}^{-1} \\\\<br>& 2.29 \\times 10^3 \\mathrm{~m} \\mathrm{~S} \\mathrm{dm}^2 \\mathrm{~mol}^{-1} \\\\<br>& =22.9 \\times 10^2 \\mathrm{~m} \\mathrm{~S} \\mathrm{dm}^2 \\mathrm{~mol}^{-1} \\\\<br>& =23 \\times 10^2 \\mathrm{~m} \\mathrm{~S} \\mathrm{dm}^2 \\mathrm{~mol}^{-1}<br />\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (2 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":29329,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Electrochemistry","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{Fe}, \\mathrm{Ni}, \\mathrm{Ag}$ will be oxidized due to lower S.R.P.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":29493,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Electrochemistry","question":"","options":["$\\wedge^{\\circ}$ of $\\mathrm{NaCl}$","$\\wedge^{\\circ}$ of $\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOK}$","The limiting equivalent conductance of $\\mathrm{H}^{+}\\left(\\wedge_{\\mathrm{H}^{+}}^{\\circ}\\right)$","$\\wedge^{\\circ}$ of chloroacetic acid $\\left(\\mathrm{C} / \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{COOH}\\right)$"],"answer":0,"solution":"From Kohlrausch's law\n$\\Lambda_{\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOH}}^{\\circ}=\\Lambda_{\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COONa}}^{\\circ}+\\Lambda_{\\mathrm{HCl}}^{\\circ}-\\Lambda_{\\mathrm{NaCl}}^{\\circ}$\nHence, (A) is the correct answer.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":29388,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Electrochemistry","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>(i)&nb